name: FallingPoints
statement: You are given a int[] X containing the x-coordinates of several points. Each point starts at an infinitely high y-coordinate. Starting with the first point, each point falls down until it is either a distance of R away from a previously fallen point or it reaches y = 0. Each point (after the first point) will start falling only when the previous one stops. Return a double[], where the i-th element is the final y-coordinate of the i-th point.
constraints: X will contain between 1 and 50 elements, inclusive.
All elements of X will be between 0 and 1,000, inclusive.
R will be between 1 and 1,000, inclusive.

examples.comment: There is only one point and it will just fall down.
Both points will fall down.
The first point falls down. The second point stops at a distance of 10 away from the first point.
